        <abstract> 
<p>Credits himself with stimulating most of the American work on plant cross-fertilisation. Sends his review of <hi rend="italic">Cross and self-fertilisation</hi> [in <hi rend="italic">Penn Monthly</hi> (June 1877)]. Suggests CD, A. Gray, and TM now agree on the extent of self-fertilisation in nature.</p> 
        </abstract>
